scoringPlays.text: Nate Iese 10 Yd pass from Josh Rosen (JJ Molson Kick)
JJ Arcega-Whiteside 8 Yd pass from Ryan Burns (Conrad Ukropina Kick)

videos.description: Ryan Burns pass intercepted Kenny Young return for 40 yds to the Stanf 26
videos.headline: R. Burns pass intercepted, K. Young return  for 40 yds

videos.description: After a turnover gives the Bruins a short field, UCLA cashes in with Nate Iese just getting over the goal line for the 10-yard score to go up 7-3 on Stanford.
videos.headline: UCLA takes the lead on Iese's 10-yard TD

videos.description: Ryan Burns pass complete to Francis Owusu for 17 yds Francis Owusu fumbled, forced by Tahaan Goodman, recovered by UCLA Adarius Pickett
videos.headline: Stanford WR Francis Owusu injured on hit to the helmet. No penalty for targeting. Owusu would be brought to the locker room following the play.

videos.description: Stanford WR Francis Owusu makes a catch then gets hit in the head by UCLA DB Tahaan Goodman forcing Owusu to fumble the ball away. Owusu remains down and heads to the locker room after the play. Referees rule no targeting on the play.
videos.headline: Stanford WR gets hit in head, no targeting foul called

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Stanford WR gets hit in head, no targeting foul called) 2016/09/24

videos.description: Josh Rosen pass incomplete to Ishmael Adams
videos.headline: Ishmael Adams drops wide-open pass for 1st down

videos.description: Ryan Burns pass complete to Trenton Irwin for 15 yds to the UCLA 19 for a 1ST down
videos.headline: R. Burns pass,to T. Irwin for 15 yds for a 1ST down

videos.description: After being stymied nearly all game,  Ryan Burns throws the fade to JJ Arcega-Whiteside for his first career touchdown catch putting Stanford ahead 16-13 with 24 seconds remaining.
videos.headline: Arcega-Whiteside the hero with final minute TD for Stanford

videos.description: Up 16-13, Stanford sacks UCLA QB Joey Alfieri and Stanford's Solomon Thomas goes 42 yards for the touchdown to seal the Cardinals' 22-13 win.
videos.headline: Stanford forces sack, returns fumble to punctuate win over UCLA
